title: The Pilot
description: A beautiful actress falls in love with Jay, but he worries that she just wants a good review for her latest film.

title: Marty's First Date
description: Jay chaperones Marty's first date, but when the girl returns to her home country, Marty decides to follow her.

title: Dial 'M' for Mother
description: As part of an effort to make Jay more likable, Geraldo Rivera interviews Jay and Eleanor, but a confrontation during the interview only makes the situation worse.

title: Miserable
description: Jay's romance with a projectionist goes bad after she ties him to a bed and plans to kill him.

title: A Little Deb Will Do You
description: Eleanor forces Margo to attend a d√©butante ball, to which Jay accompanies her; meanwhile, Jay's show is losing viewers to a children's show called "Humphrey the Hippo."

title: Eyes on the Prize
description: After Jay gets fired due to low ratings, his goal is to rebuild his career by winning a second Pulitzer Prize.

roles.char: Adolph Hitmaker, Bernie Wasserman, Prof. Blowhard

title: Every Doris Has Her Day
description: Jay becomes friends with Doris the makeup lady and eventually comes to believe that she is his birth mother.

title: Marathon Mensch
description: After being mocked for his poor physical condition, Jay decides to run the New York Marathon to prove he is a man.

title: L.A. Jay
description: After writing a screenplay, Jay takes leave from his job and moves to Hollywood, where he is hired to write a sequel to a movie he hated.

title: Dr. Jay
description: Duke wants to give up on life after learning he has only four years to live, but Jay tries to find a cure for his ailment.

title: A Day at the Races and a Night at the Opera
description: Jay tries to help Marty find something he is good at, and Duke promises viewers $100 each if Jay can't make them laugh.

title: Uneasy Rider
description: Jay quits his job as a critic and becomes a truck driver.

title: A Pig Boy and His Dog
description: Eleanor writes a children's book whose main character is based on Jay.

title: Sherman, Woman and Child
description: Romance blooms when Jay takes in poor woman and her child.

title: Siskel & Ebert & Jay & Alice
description: Gene Siskel and Roger Ebert break up their partnership as movie critics, and each of them considers Jay as a potential replacement for the other.

title: Lady Hawke
description: Alice is jealous when Jay is courted by Jeremy's beautiful sister.

title: A Song for Margo
description: Margo falls in love with rock star Johnny Wrath, and Jay tries to help Alice find a preschool for Penny.

title: From Chunk to Hunk
description: Marty becomes popular at school after losing weight, and Jay gets a death threat after giving an actor a bad review.

title: All the Duke's Men
description: Duke runs for president of the United States with Jay as his speechwriter.

title: Sherman of Arabia
description: Jay tells Alice, Penny, Marty, and Marty's friends about how he was trapped in Iraq during the Persian Gulf War.

title: Frankie and Ellie Get Lost
description: Jay's parents are lost at sea, and Jay is put in charge of their fortune.

title: Dukerella
description: Alice's sister Randa comes to New York to find a husband and eventually sets her sights on Duke.

title: I Can't Believe It's a Clip Show
description: While hosting his 10th anniversary special at Carnegie Hall, Jay is taken hostage on stage and shows numerous film clips while awaiting rescue.
